name: scikit-plot
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "scikit-plot" %}
{% set version = "0.3.7" %}
{% set sha256 = "2c7948817fd2dc06879cfe3c1fdde56a8e71fa5ac626ffbe79f043650baa6242" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 1
  script: python -m pip install .

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python
    - matplotlib-base
    - scikit-learn
    - scipy
    - joblib

test:
  imports:
    - scikitplot
    - scikitplot.plotters
    - scikitplot.helpers
    - scikitplot.classifiers
    - scikitplot.clustering
    - scikitplot.estimators
    - scikitplot.cluster
    - scikitplot.decomposition
    - scikitplot.metrics

about:
  home: https://github.com/reiinakano/scikit-plot/
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'An intuitive library to add plotting functionality to scikit-learn objects.'
  doc_url: scikit-plot.readthedocs.io/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ericmjl
    - reiinakano
